  "commentary": "With SPX at 7090.61 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7096, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and will be selling any push higher while buying dips, creating natural resistance. The massive +7.3B gamma wall at 7200 acts as a strong magnet, but the thick positive gamma layers at 7100 (+5B) and 7150 (+5.1B) will dampen volatility and create stepping stone resistance on any rally attempt. Key levels to watch: 7096 flip point for regime change, 7040 max negative gamma support, and the 7200 gamma wall as the primary upside target.\n\nBottom line: expect sticky price action with a slow grind toward 7200 but limited downside below 7040.",
